<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4907] strong named assemblies wanted</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4907</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2947&quot; title=&quot;Using Apache code signing service to sign the Thrift NuGet project&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-2947&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-2947&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a strong name should have been added to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nuget.org/packages/ApacheThrift/0.12.0.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.nuget.org/packages/ApacheThrift/0.12.0.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the DLL, it&apos;s not signed at all. The assembly name is still `Thrift, Version=0.12.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null` and therefore missing the `PublicKeyToken` part.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
